### HYMN LXXXV

#### A charm against Consumption

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_0608501">1</span></span>Let Varana
the heavenly tree here present keep disease away.  
  The Gods have driven off Decline that entered and possessed  
   this man. <span id="page_a240">p. a240</span>  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_0608502">2</span></span>We with the
speech of Indra and of Mitra and of Varuna.  
  We with the speech of all the Gods will drive Decline away from  
   thee.  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_0608503">3</span></span>Even as
Vritra checked and stayed these waters flowing every  
   way,  
  With Agni, God of all mankind. I check and banish thy Decline.

